{"UNDID":[{"def":"Un*did\", Defn: imp.","pos":""}],"UNDIFFERENTIATED":[{"def":"Not differentiated; specifically (Biol.","pos":""}],"UNDIGENOUS":[{"def":"Generated by water.","pos":""}],"UNDIGHT":[{"def":"To put off; to lay aside, as a garment.","pos":""}],"UNDINE":[{"def":"One of a class of fabled female water spirits who might receive a human soul by intermarrying with a mortal.","pos":""}],"UNDIOCESED":[{"def":"Unprovided with a diocese; having no diocese.","pos":""}],"UNDIRECT":[{"def":"To misdirect; to mislead.","pos":""}],"UNDIRECTED":[{"def":"Not directed; not guided; left without direction.","pos":""},{"def":"Not addressed; not superscribed, as a letter.","pos":""}],"UNDISCERNING":[{"def":"Want of discernment.","pos":""}],"UNDISCLOSE":[{"def":"To keep close or secret.","pos":""}],"UNDISPENSABLE":[{"def":"Unavoidable; inevitable.","pos":""}],"UNDISPENSED":[{"def":"Not freed by dispensation.","pos":""}],"UNDISPOSEDNESS":[{"def":"Indisposition; disinclination.","pos":""}],"UNDISTINCTIVE":[{"def":"Making no distinctions; not discriminating; impartial.","pos":""}],"UNDIVIDED":[{"def":"Not lobed, cleft, or branched; entire.","pos":""}],"UNDIVIDUAL":[{"def":"True courage and courtesy are undividual companions.","pos":""}]}